Indocement, Indo Tambangraya, XL: Indonesia Equity Preview

-- B y   B e r n i   M o e s t a f a
-- 
2011-08-12T01:49:06Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-08-12/indocement-indo-tambangraya-xl-indonesia-equity-preview.html
Shares of the following companies
may have unusual moves in Indonesian trading. Stock symbols are
in parentheses, and share prices are as of the previous close.  The  Jakarta Composite index (JCI)  rose 0.2 percent to 3,869.37.  PT XL Axiata (EXCL IJ): The unit of Malaysia’s Axiata Group
Bhd. is seeking a 1 trillion-rupiah ($117 million) loan to help
refinance total debt of 2.5 trillion rupiah this year, Kontan
reported, citing Finance Director Willem Timmermans. XL Axiata
fell 2.8 percent to 5,150 rupiah.  PT Indocement Tunggal Prakarsa (INTP IJ):  Indonesia ’s
second-biggest cement producer plans to spend $1.17 billion
through 2017 to boost capacity, Bisnis Indonesia reported,
citing President Director Daniel Lavalle. Production capacity
will increase to 27.1 million metric tons a year, the report
said. Indocement declined 2.4 percent to 14,450 rupiah.  PT Indo Tambangraya Megah (ITMG IJ): The company’s first-
half net income rose to $205.3 million from $134.1 million a
year earlier, the Indonesian unit of  Thailand ’s biggest coal
producer, Banpu Pcl, said in a statement published in  Bisnis
Indonesia . Indo Tambangraya fell 2 percent to 43,950 rupiah.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Berni Moestafa in Jakarta at 
